Evangeline Lilly played Tauriel, an Elven warrior and Legolas's love interest, who was created for The Hobbit film series by Peter Jackson and Philippa Boyens.
She is a skilled fighter, having been trained since she was young to fight orcs, and is one of the only female Woodland Elves known to be skilled in combat. As a member of King Thranduil's royal guard, Tauriel falls in love with Kíli after he is captured by her king. Though their relationship remains unfulfilled due to his death at the Battle of Five Armies, Tauriel helps Legolas flee Mirkwood during Smaug's attack on Laketown. In the Extended Edition of The Desolation of Smaug, she is shown to have feelings for Legolas as well.
In addition to being an important character in the narrative of the films, Tauriel has garnered significant attention from audiences, particularly within fandom communities focused on romance between the female elf and Legolas (Legiola). Some fans consider her to be the first major lesbian character portrayed in a high-profile Hollywood adaptation of J.R.R. Tolkien's Middle-earth stories,[6][7] while others dispute this categorization due to ambiguous evidence about Tauriel's sexuality. Critical reception towards Tauriel has been mixed; some critics commend her strong personality and action sequences, but others criticize her role for existing solely to serve the main male characters.
